    "text": "Woodhaven Boulevard (Trotting Course Lane), at the N.E. corner of Fleet Street (White Pot Road), showing the Whitepot School House. It appears in the J. L. Riker map of 1852 and still appears as a school house in 1891. In 1909, G. Lappe owned this corner and the buildings thereon. The school house does not appear in the Queens Atlas of 1929.\n\n---\nArthur White.\n",
